==Electric Generator== An electric generator is an electromagnetic device that can produce alternate current electric (AC) through the interaction of an electromagnet and a conventional magnet.
==Construction & Operation== : [[File:Elementary_Two_Phase_Alternator.jpg|400px]]
==Reference== {{wikipedia|Electric generator}} {{BookCat}}

==Permanent Electromagnetic Magnet== A permanent magnet is an electromagnetic that does not lose its magnetic field when the current is zero
===Permanent Electromagnet Properties=== # A magnet has two "poles" namely north pole and south pole. # The magnetic field is made up of magnetic field lines that travels from north pole to south pole # The magnetic field Strength is the product of the coil's inductance and current. B = L I # Magnet of same poles repel; different poles attract
