=== Cinema and TV ===
'''Last Stand of the Templars''' (4 Apr. 2011) a National Geographic Channel documentary. Featuring a contemporaneous examination of the Battle at Jacob's Fordone, a crucial part of the Templars' past by Dr. Ronnie Ellenblum and his archaeological team.

'''[[w:Ironclad (film)|Ironclad]]'''([http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1233301/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1 IMDB]) (2011) a fictional movie based in the historic facts of 13th-century (1215) England. Portraying Church, Templars and the general English political situation, in particular King John's response to the Magna Carta and the subsequent [[w:Rochester_castle#King_John|battle for  Rochester Castle]].

